- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper specifically addresses the need for developing algorithms in a distributed memory architecture due to the explosion in the size of data. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a novel algorithmic framework for solving the Nonnegative Matrix Factorization problem. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper involves mathematical optimization techniques for solving the Nonnegative Matrix Factorization problem. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper presents numerical experiments to verify the correctness, efficiency, and scalability of the proposed algorithm.
